    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 22 with a lineup anchored by high-ceiling, high-volume contributors in favorable spots. **Yordan Alvarez** (73.68) remains our premier start against Bibee; his elite xwOBA (0.393) and prime spot in the two-hole against a middle-of-the-road xERA (4.15) create the day\u2019s highest floor. Similarly, **Kyle Schwarber** (70.97) and **Junior Caminero** (68.80) are clear \"Strong\" plays. **Kyle Schwarber** benefits from a dynamic platoon edge batting leadoff, while **Junior Caminero** faces the softest matchup of the day in Williamson (5.40 xERA). Though **Trea Turner** (67.78) faces a slight drag on his SB probability due to the catcher's arm strength, his speed and spot in the order keep him in the elite tier of today's production projections.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card was the final utility spot, where **Josh Smith** (43.86) narrowly missed the cut behind **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (47.99). While **Josh Smith** possesses a desirable dynamic platoon advantage against Ashcraft, the raw projected efficiency favored the defensive and speed upside of **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, despite the latter\u2019s lower order slot and a penalty for opposing catcher pop-time. We are keeping a close watch on **Victor Scott II** (48.80), whose output is heavily contingent on his ability to neutralize the catcher in his stolen base attempts; as our primary SB catalyst, he is a start despite his bottom-of-the-order ranking. Owners should note that **Christian Yelich** remains sidelined, and with **Colt Keith** and **Zac Veen** currently unavailable due to benching or minor league status, the depth of our bench is being tested, leaving little margin for error should weather or late-scratch announcements plague the slate.",
